=== BUSTOK ===
//axhob_operation
{bust_knock}

NOTE: Probes workload responsiveness via passwordless SSH.
Used to confirm that a workload {burn_regime} profile is currently
usable before dispatching real work, and used internally by the
garrison and conscript ceremonies as their final verification step.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burn_regime} profile exists at the given {burn_alias} and references
a {burn_key_file} readable by the calling {burs_user}.

//axhos_step
. *Open SSH connection*: invoke the SSH client non-interactively using
the profile's {burn_alias} and {burn_key_file}

//axhos_step
. *Issue trivial command*: execute a no-op remote command (e.g.,
`true`) and observe the remote exit status

//axhog_guarantee
No remote OS state was modified.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the remote command returns 0 within the probe window.
Non-zero on connection refusal, authentication failure, remote-exec
failure, or probe-window timeout.
=== BUSTOE ===
//axhob_operation
{bust_remote_run}

NOTE: Executes the contents of a local command file on the remote node
and captures stdout, stderr, and the remote exit status to
{burd_output_dir}.
Workload-tier dispatch.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{busi_scribed_command_file}

//axhoq_precondition
A workload-tier {burn_regime} profile exists at the given {burn_alias}
and is currently {bust_knock}-responsive.

//axhoq_precondition
The local command file referenced as the dispatch input exists and is
readable by the calling user.

//axhos_step
. *Open workload session*: open an SSH session using the workload
profile

//axhos_step
. *Stream command file*: feed the command-file contents to the remote
shell

//axhos_step
. *Capture outputs*: write remote stdout, stderr, and the remote exit
status to {burd_output_dir}

//axhog_guarantee
The complete remote stdout, stderr, and exit code are durably written
under {burd_output_dir} regardless of the remote command's success or
failure.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when dispatch and capture both complete (independent of the
remote exit code).
Non-zero on SSH connection failure, capture-write failure, or transport
interruption.
=== BUSTOS ===
//axhob_operation
{bust_interactive_session}

NOTE: Opens an interactive SSH session to the workload account named
by a workload {burn_regime} profile.
Foreground operation; control returns to the station shell when the
operator exits the remote shell.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
A workload-tier {burn_regime} profile exists at the given {burn_alias}
and is currently {bust_knock}-responsive.

//axhos_step
. *Hand control to SSH*: invoke the local SSH client interactively
against the workload account

//axhos_step
. *Wait for exit*: block until the operator exits the remote shell

//axhog_guarantee
No artifact is written to {burd_output_dir} — interactive sessions
deliberately bypass dispatch capture.
No local profile is modified.

//axhoc_completion
Exit code mirrors the SSH client's exit code when the session ends
normally.
Non-zero on connection or authentication failure before the session
opens.
=== BUSTHT ===
//axhob_operation
{bust_handbook_node_top}

NOTE: Top-level landing surface for the Remote Node Access handbook.
Renders handbook prose to the operator's terminal as the entry point
into the per-platform garrison and conscript procedures.
No remote contact and no profile mutation.

//axhos_step
. *Render landing*: emit the node-access handbook landing content,
including pointers to per-platform garrison and conscript procedures

//axhog_guarantee
No remote contact occurred and no local file was written.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 after the landing content is printed.
Non-zero only when the handbook content cannot be located or rendered.

